The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 23: The government is working on a Rs 2,300-crore bailout package for Air India, which has suffered a Rs 2,144-crore loss last fiscal due to rising jet fuel prices and operational costs. The package includes Rs 1,300 crore as equity and Rs 1,000-crore soft loan. The National Aviation Company is preparing the package that will be produced before the cabinet for approval.                            
	 Geneva, July 23: Softening its stand on the US offer, India today described the American proposal to reduce its farm aid as a good sign and hoped developed nations will make similar moves in other areas for reaching a breakthrough in the WTO talks.                            
	 Calcutta, July 23: The Indian Chamber of Commerce has opened its first office in New Delhi. Offices will also be opened in Bhubaneswar and Patna, which will be operational this year.                             
	 Mumbai, July 23: The hearing of the dispute between the Ambani brothers over the supply of gas from the KG-basin will be held on a day-to-day basis from tomorrow by Bombay High Court.                            
	 New Delhi, July 23: SBI is planning to hire 3,000 marketing and recovery officers in its second such recruitment drive in less than a year.                                                                                                                         
